# Workflow Build Targets

The workflow system supports two build targets, configured in [packages/cli/src/index.ts](mdc:packages/cli/src/index.ts):

## 1. vercel-static (Default)

The default build target that creates static bundles:

```typescript
// Output paths
stepsBundlePath: './api/generated/steps.js'
workflowBundle: './api/generated/workflows.js'
```

This target is used when:
- No target is specified: `wf`
- Explicitly set: `wf --target vercel-static`
- Running in example app: `pnpm build`

## 2. vercel-build-output-api

Creates a Vercel Build Output API structure in `.vercel/output/`:

```typescript
// Output directory
buildOutputDir: './.vercel/output'

// Function paths
.vercel/output/functions/api/generated/steps.func/
.vercel/output/functions/api/generated/workflows.func/
```

This target is used when explicitly specified:
```bash
wf --target vercel-build-output-api
```

## Configuration

The build configuration is defined in [packages/cli/src/index.ts](mdc:packages/cli/src/index.ts) and processes workflow files from:
- [apps/example/workflows/steps.ts](mdc:apps/example/workflows/steps.ts)
- [apps/example/workflows/workflows.ts](mdc:apps/example/workflows/workflows.ts)

Both targets ensure the functions are accessible at:
- `/api/generated/steps`
- `/api/generated/workflows`
